  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b0adbc23-4ad6-4321-b096-bcc0fda5f112",
    "name": "Finance Dashboard",
    "description": "A complete test collection for the Finance Dashboard Node.js/Express API running on `http://localhost:3000`.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. Run the Login request inside the **Auth** folder. The post-response script will automatically save the `token` collection variable.\n2. All protected routes use `{{token}}` as the Bearer token via collection-level auth.\n3. For role-based tests, run **Login as Viewer** in the **Role Testing** folder to populate `{{viewer_token}}`.\n\n## Collection Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `token` | Admin/default user JWT, set automatically by the Login request |\n| `viewer_token` | Viewer-role JWT, set automatically by Login as Viewer |\n\n## Auth\n\nCollection-level auth is set to **Bearer Token** using `{{token}}`. All requests in the Auth and Health folders override this with **No Auth**.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "33612001",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/33612001-b0adbc23-4ad6-4321-b096-bcc0fda5f112?source=collection_link"
  },
